        "text": "They turned",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; manifestly an improvement on the A.V., as giving the sense of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "οἵτινες",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", viz. that all who saw the paralytic walking, turned, as a consequence, to the Lord, in whose Name the wonderful miracle had been wrought. A very extensive conversion of the people of Lydda and of Sharon is signified. Acts 9:35",
        "children": []
      },
